Youth for Social Impact

From Ideas to Ventures: Youth Shaping the Future

Empowering the youth with 21st-century skills to co-create innovative, scalable, and sustainable solutions that address local challenges. By fostering an entrepreneurial mindset, we enable the youth to lead impactful ventures that solve real-world challenges and drive social and economic transformation.

Login Register

ABOUT

Youth for Social Impact

This Program aims to empower India’s youth with the entrepreneurial skills and mindsets needed to drive innovation and create impactful, scalable ventures. By equipping young people with 21st-century skills, we enable them to address real-world challenges and transform problems into opportunities for growth and development.

Program focuses on fostering innovation & entrepreneurship by guiding youth through the process of ideation, innovation, and venture creation. Through mentorship, hands-on learning, and exposure to industry leaders, we provide young people with the tools they need to build sustainable

ventures that not only solve real-world challenges but also contribute to economic and social development.

Our mission is to build a generation of youth innovators & entrepreneurs who are ready to lead the future of innovation, economic growth, and sustainable impact.

ROAD MAP

Journey Of The Student

THEMES

No problem is too big... No idea is too small

Smart Automation

Innovate using AI and advanced technologies to optimize systems and resources across industries.

Fitness & Sports

Develop solutions that promote health, fitness, and enhance sports performance.

Heritage & Culture

Create ventures that showcase and preserve India’s rich cultural heritage.

MedTech / BioTech / HealthTech

Innovations in healthcare, biotech, and health technology to address modern health challenges.

Agriculture & Rural Development

Solutions aimed at boosting agricultural productivity and rural development through tech innovations.

Smart Vehicles

Design intelligent vehicle systems to revolutionize transportation.

Transportation & Logistics

Propose ideas to enhance transportation networks and logistics infrastructure.

Robotics & Drones

Innovate in robotics and drone technology to address challenges like rescue operations and logistics.

Clean & Green Technology

Sustainable solutions for waste management, clean energy, and environmental preservation.

Tourism

Ideas to rejuvenate the tourism industry by enhancing travel, hospitality, and cultural experiences.

Renewable & Sustainable Energy

Develop innovations in renewable energy sources and sustainability to drive future energy solutions.

Blockchain & Cybersecurity

Leverage blockchain and cybersecurity innovations to protect data and enhance digital security.

Smart Education

Innovate in education through smart technologies and digital platforms for improved learning.

Disaster Management

Create solutions that improve disaster risk mitigation, planning, and recovery efforts.

Toys & Games

Develop innovative toys and games inspired by India’s cultural and historical richness.

Miscellaneous

Submit technology-driven ideas in sectors like hospitality, financial services, and retail.

Space Technology

Innovations in space technology and exploration to push the frontiers of science and engineering.

Financial Inclusion & FinTech

Develop solutions to enhance financial literacy, inclusion, and access to financial services.

Rural Innovation & Development

Develop solutions that promote health, fitness, and enhance sports performance.

Public Governance & CivicTech

Create technology-driven solutions to improve governance, public services, and civic engagement.

Others

Encourages innovative solutions in any other areas.

FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

  • Who can participate in the program?

    Youth aged 17-25 who are passionate about innovation and entrepreneurship can participate.

  • What types of ideas can I submit?

    Ideas that align with one of the 20 provided themes, including Smart Automation, HealthTech, Agriculture, Education, etc.

  • Can I participate as an individual?

    YES, BUT team participation is encouraged.

  • What is the selection process?

    Ideas are evaluated based on innovation, impact, feasibility, and scalability. Shortlisted teams move to the next phase.

  • Is there mentorship available?

    Yes, shortlisted teams receive mentorship from industry experts to refine their ideas.

  • What support is provided to the winning ideas?

    Winning teams receive incubation support, funding, and resources to grow and scale their ventures.

  • How do I submit my idea?

    After registering your team, complete the course, select a theme, and submit your idea through the online portal.

  • What are the key phases of the program?

    The program has two main phases: Ideation and Evaluation, followed by the Entrepreneurship Journey, including mentorship, pitching, and incubation.

  • Can I submit more than one idea?

    No, each team can submit only one idea aligned with a specific theme.

  • What is the timeline for the program?

    Details on program phases, deadlines, and submission dates are available on the about us section.
